INSERT INTO dashboard_public.actions ( owner_id, title, slug, url, photo, location, is_approved, is_published, is_private, self_verifiable, is_recurring, limited_to_location, once_per_object, minimum_group_members, start_date, end_date, description, call_to_action, discovery_header, discovery_description, completed_action_text, activity_feed_text, already_completed_action_text, time_required, recurring_interval ) VALUES ('b00cc061-691d-593f-8362-066af58b777f', 'The Mission to Cool LA', inflection.slugify('The Mission to Cool LA'), 'https://www.scpr.org/news/2017/07/10/73657/roofs-streets-and-trees-how-la-is-trying-to-lower/', '{"url":"https://dl.airtable.com/.attachments/ba906e0048777b62be93b3cc0f128bfe/3ee49be6/image.png","filename":"image.png","size":1146353,"mime":"image/png"}'::jsonb, NULL, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE, NULL, '2020-11-13T08:00:00.000Z', '2021-02-28T08:00:00.000Z', '## What
Like most big cities, Los Angeles literally creates its own climate. Buildings and asphalt absorb and radiate heat, raising summer temperatures by as much as 19 degrees in some parts of the region. According to CalEPA, LA has the worst urban heat island effect of any region in California.

Excessive heat is deadly. Heat stroke, heat exhaustion, difficulty breathing, cramping and general discomfort killed more people between 1979 and 2003 than hurricanes, lightning, tornadoes, floods and earthquakes combined, according to the Centers for Diseases Control and Prevention. 

The number of extremely hot days is expected to triple by mid-century. That’s why LA Mayor Eric Garcetti has the goal of lowering this urban heat island effect three degrees by 2035. 

Can the city do it? 

[Read more](https://www.scpr.org/news/2017/07/10/73657/roofs-streets-and-trees-how-la-is-trying-to-lower/)', 'Read it', 'Why?', 'L.A. is the one just two major cities worldwide with a temperature reduction target (the other is Melbourne).', 'I''ve read it ', 'learned about the plan to cool LA', NULL, '300 seconds'::interval, '0 seconds'::interval);

INSERT INTO dashboard_public.actions ( owner_id, title, slug, url, photo, location, is_approved, is_published, is_private, self_verifiable, is_recurring, limited_to_location, once_per_object, minimum_group_members, start_date, end_date, description, call_to_action, discovery_header, discovery_description, completed_action_text, activity_feed_text, already_completed_action_text, time_required, recurring_interval ) VALUES ('b6fdd89e-47d8-590b-a918-0314b29badc5', 'Volunteer With KYCC''s Environmental Team', inflection.slugify('Volunteer With KYCC''s Environmental Team'), 'http://www.kyccla.org/services/environmental-services/environmental-team-volunteers/', '{"url":"https://dl.airtable.com/.attachments/51df5b48e927dde7a8d6110fdda2d02b/b3aaf7ba/comm-beaut-2.jpg","filename":"comm-beaut-2.jpg","size":71820,"mime":"image/jpeg"}'::jsonb, NULL, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE, NULL, '2020-11-13T08:00:00.000Z', '2021-02-28T08:00:00.000Z', '## What
KYCC has many community-led volunteer projects.  These fun, family-friendly events typically run from 9 a.m. to noon and involve tree planting, graffiti removal, and community beautification.  If you would like to volunteer with us, please see our opportunities listed below.

For more information on any of our volunteer opportunities, please contact KYCC’s us [here.](https://www.tfaforms.com/4767908)

**Become a Volunteer Team Leader**
KYCC’s community volunteer events are fantastic because of the help of our dedicated Volunteer Team Leaders (VTL).  VTLs are the backbone of our community events, by providing support to KYCC staff and supervising other volunteers. If you are looking to be a leader in your community, and can make a long-term commitment to help others to beautify Los Angeles, we want you on our team! VTLs must attend a half-day Saturday training and be 14 years and older. We would like for VTLs to attend at least three events per year. 

**Group Volunteer Opportunities**
Let KYCC’s Environmental Services team create a fun, hands-on, and meaningful group volunteer experience in Koreatown!  Whether you have a group of 10 or 100, KYCC will work with you to create a service experience that builds your team and meets your community engagement goals.

During a KYCC group beautification project, a dedicated staff member will train and supervise your team. We take care of all city permits, and supply all the necessary tools and safety equipment.  Typical service projects include graffiti removal, tree planting, tree care, and other community beautification activities.

Join us at one of our upcoming [events.](http://www.kyccla.org/events/)

Or, if you are interested in hosting your own event:

**Community Volunteer Opportunities**
Live in Koreatown or a surrounding area and want to help beautify your neighborhood? Or maybe you live in another area but are passionate about beautifying underserved areas in Los Angeles? If so we would be happy to have you at our beautification or tree planting events! Most of our events typically take place on a Saturday and are 3-4 hours. We provide the tools and snacks, you just bring yourself, closed toe shoes and clothes you can get dirty in!

Join us at one of our upcoming [events.](http://www.kyccla.org/events/)

**Participate in our Annual Cleanup Day**
We host an annual large community cleanup day with our neighbors and friends. We are passionate about keeping our streets clean in Koreatown, Westlake and Pico-Union! We provide all the tools and equipment to paint, pressure wash, pull weeds and pick up trash. Join us and our community friends and neighbors! 

**Internship Opportunitie**s
The Koreatown Youth and Community Center (KYCC) is one of the leading organizations that plants trees in the City of Los Angeles and we can use your help!  Whether it’s assisting in our free tree distributions, leading a team of volunteers, supporting our tree planting or beautification events, removing graffiti, or helping around the office we have a job for you.  Our internship is ideal for students, people that are passionate about environmental issues, or those looking to develop professional skills.  Interns must be at least 18 years old and be able to commit at least 12 hours per week for a minimum of 3 months.

[Learn more and sign up](https://www.tfaforms.com/4767908) ', 'Sign Up', 'Why?', 'Improve your neighborhood and learn new skills to regenerate land. KYCC’s community volunteer events are fantastic because of the help of our dedicated Volunteer Team Leaders (VTL).', 'I''ve done it ', 'helped out plant trees with KYCC', NULL, '600 seconds'::interval, '0 seconds'::interval);

