INSERT INTO dashboard_public.actions ( owner_id, title, slug, url, photo, location, is_approved, is_published, is_private, self_verifiable, is_recurring, limited_to_location, once_per_object, minimum_group_members, start_date, end_date, description, call_to_action, discovery_header, discovery_description, completed_action_text, activity_feed_text, already_completed_action_text, time_required, recurring_interval ) VALUES ('3a09606a-4110-59bc-ac10-94074569c1f7', 'Install a Rotating Sprinkler Nozzle', inflection.slugify('Install a Rotating Sprinkler Nozzle'), 'https://dpw.lacounty.gov/wwd/web/Conservation/RebateProgram.aspx', '{"url":"https://dl.airtable.com/.attachments/4ceaee30a32d0f8ab77302363c437a55/55d96ac0/ROtatingsprink.jpg","filename":"ROtating sprink.jpg","size":30045,"mime":"image/jpeg"}'::jsonb, NULL, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE, NULL, '2021-02-13T00:21:00.000Z', '2021-12-31T08:20:00.000Z', '## What

The latest innovation in sprinkler technology are nozzles that turn a standard pop-up spray head into a precision device that can save water in your landscape. In addition, water jetting from these nozzles is more resistant to wind, less
likely to mist, and significantly reduces run-off onto streets and sidewalks. 

These nozzles shoot multi-trajectory, rotating streams that apply water more slowly and uniformly than conventional sprays and heads especially when adjusted for specific site
conditions. Rotating nozzles use less water than traditional spray heads because they operate with lower precipitation rates and have greater distribution uniformity. In many cases, you can update your existing sprinkler heads with new rotary nozzles without having to replace the entire sprinkler body. Also, rotating nozzles have greater coverage. [Read more](http://www.bewaterwise.com/assets/rotating_nozzles_brochure_2014.pdf#:~:text=Rotating%20nozzles%20use%20less%20water%20than%20traditional%20spray,sprinkler%20body.%20Also%2C%20rotating%20nozzles%20have%20greater%20coverage.)

