[Apply Here](https://dpw.lacounty.gov/wwd/web/Conservation/RebateProgram.aspx)', 'Apply', 'Why?', 'Learn about how you can get a rebate from The Waterworks Districts for installing weather-based irrigation controllers.', 'I''ve applied', 'applied for a WBIC rebate', NULL, '900 seconds'::interval, '0 seconds'::interval);

INSERT INTO dashboard_public.actions ( owner_id, title, slug, url, photo, location, is_approved, is_published, is_private, self_verifiable, is_recurring, limited_to_location, once_per_object, minimum_group_members, start_date, end_date, description, call_to_action, discovery_header, discovery_description, completed_action_text, activity_feed_text, already_completed_action_text, time_required, recurring_interval ) VALUES ('adcfeb98-7aef-5c3b-8cf3-523e62d3b7de', 'A Beginner''s Guide To Biking in La', inflection.slugify('A Beginner''s Guide To Biking in La'), 'https://laist.com/2019/05/23/a_beginners_guide_to_biking_in_la.php', '{"url":"https://dl.airtable.com/.attachments/780e4b3ba193323ebc3c6fad531e6741/23e33fbf/image.png","filename":"image.png","size":596371,"mime":"image/png"}'::jsonb, NULL, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE, NULL, '2020-11-13T08:00:00.000Z', '2021-02-28T08:00:00.000Z', '## What
Biking is becoming an increasingly popular activity in Los Angeles, as more and more Angelenos get into healthy, low-cost and zero-emission two-wheeled transportation. California is ranked fourth out of the 50 states for its number of bike-to-work commuters, and Caltrans and the California Bicycle Coalition hope to see 4.5% of all trips taken by bike by 2020 in an effort to reduce traffic and pollution.

With the novice cyclist in mind, here is a beginner''s guide to biking in L.A, complete with safety and maintenance tips, info on where to ride and places to go, apps to help you get around, and nonprofit groups that are making Los Angeles a better, safer city for bike riders. 

[Read more](https://laist.com/2019/05/23/a_beginners_guide_to_biking_in_la.php)', 'Read it', 'Why?', 'With the novice cyclist in mind, here is a beginner''s guide to biking in L.A, complete with safety and maintenance tips, info on where to ride and places to go...', 'I''ve read it ', 'is thinking about biking', NULL, '120 seconds'::interval, '0 seconds'::interval);

INSERT INTO dashboard_public.actions ( owner_id, title, slug, url, photo, location, is_approved, is_published, is_private, self_verifiable, is_recurring, limited_to_location, once_per_object, minimum_group_members, start_date, end_date, description, call_to_action, discovery_header, discovery_description, completed_action_text, activity_feed_text, already_completed_action_text, time_required, recurring_interval ) VALUES ('b13d2f4d-9d72-552a-ac26-17824db1068b', 'Volunteer with MPA Watch', inflection.slugify('Volunteer with MPA Watch'), 'https://www.lawaterkeeper.org/mpa-watch-sign-up', '{"url":"https://dl.airtable.com/.attachments/a46d24a9d6717a4d4260cc59702636a1/59f844d0/mpa.JPG","filename":"mpa.JPG","size":24952,"mime":"image/jpeg"}'::jsonb, NULL, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE, NULL, '2021-05-12T21:01:00.000Z', '2022-01-01T05:01:00.000Z', '## What 

As the first on- the-water MPA Watch program in California, and the only source of on-the-water data in Los Angeles, the program is critical to ensuring these precious habitats are protected and preserved for all to enjoy. 

While they will be operating this program primarily without volunteers, until it is safe to do so under evolving COVID-19 public health guidelines, MPA Watch typically bring more than 300 volunteers on board every year to collect critical data that helps improve management of these “underwater parks” and to provide once-in-a-lifetime experiences on the water. 

They are proud that this program promotes coastal access for students, underserved youth, volunteers and Angelenos of all stripes and look forward to reengaging volunteers to build long-term awareness and support of MPAs. Please sign up to express your interest in volunteering when community engagement with the program resumes.

MPA volunteers must be 18 years of age or 16+ to volunteer with a parent or guardian.', 'Do it ', 'Why?', 'A Marine Protected Area (MPA) is an area of the ocean where consumptive human activities, such as fishing, are limited or restricted in order to protect or conserve marine life or habitats.', 'I''ve done it ', 'volunteered with MPA watch', NULL, '7200 seconds'::interval, '0 seconds'::interval);

INSERT INTO dashboard_public.actions ( owner_id, title, slug, url, photo, location, is_approved, is_published, is_private, self_verifiable, is_recurring, limited_to_location, once_per_object, minimum_group_members, start_date, end_date, description, call_to_action, discovery_header, discovery_description, completed_action_text, activity_feed_text, already_completed_action_text, time_required, recurring_interval ) VALUES ('b13d2f4d-9d72-552a-ac26-17824db1068b', 'Participate in the Creeks 2 Coast Cleanup Challenge', inflection.slugify('Participate in the Creeks 2 Coast Cleanup Challenge'), 'https://www.lawaterkeeper.org/cleanupchallenge', '{"url":"https://dl.airtable.com/.attachments/d1a1ddc31471d40d46879f3d475f08b0/701ff6fe/cleanup.JPG","filename":"cleanup.JPG","size":62349,"mime":"image/jpeg"}'::jsonb, NULL, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE, NULL, '2021-05-12T20:56:00.000Z', '2022-01-01T04:56:00.000Z', '## What
 
Despite the ecological and community importance of these areas, we continue to find litter and debris creating negative impacts. Trash poses a threat to human health, wildlife, and our environment. Trash that is allowed to enter our waters becomes marine debris, adding to the pollution problem facing the world. By participating in the Cleanup Challenge, you will positively impact communities and outdoor spaces up and down the watershed. Let’s take the time to care for our waterways!

Challenge sites are categorized into four groups: Coastal, River & Creeks, Metropolitan Parks, and Trails. Participants pick two sites from three categories of their choice to ensure cleanup efforts improve our watershed, help diverse communities, and protect our ocean. After the first cleanup, you have one year to complete SIX total cleanups and become a Cleanup Champion. Once you’ve finished the Challenge, you will receive a certificate of completion and fun prizes! 

[Get started](https://www.lawaterkeeper.org/cleanupchallenge)', 'Do it ', 'Why?', 'Volunteers help safeguard the Marine Protected Areas off our coast, combat stormwater and plastic pollution in our neighborhoods and monitor the health of our rivers and creeks.', 'I''ve done it ', 'participated in the Creeks 2 Coast Cleanup Challenge', NULL, '7200 seconds'::interval, '0 seconds'::interval);

INSERT INTO dashboard_public.actions ( owner_id, title, slug, url, photo, location, is_approved, is_published, is_private, self_verifiable, is_recurring, limited_to_location, once_per_object, minimum_group_members, start_date, end_date, description, call_to_action, discovery_header, discovery_description, completed_action_text, activity_feed_text, already_completed_action_text, time_required, recurring_interval ) VALUES ('b13d2f4d-9d72-552a-ac26-17824db1068b', 'Join the Community Water Watch', inflection.slugify('Join the Community Water Watch'), 'https://www.lawaterkeeper.org/community-water-watch-sign-up', '{"url":"https://dl.airtable.com/.attachments/81037a731931d8f2a8e138613e556634/c3a1e989/watch.JPG","filename":"watch.JPG","size":45532,"mime":"image/jpeg"}'::jsonb, NULL, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE, NULL, '2021-05-12T21:15:00.000Z', '2022-01-01T05:15:00.000Z', '## What 

Through the Community Water Watch program (CWW), LA Water Keeper seeks to ensure that community members living in LA’s most impacted industrial areas have the tools, training, and resources to identify toxic runoff and hold polluters and regulators accountable.

While they will be operating this program primarily without volunteers, until it is safe to do so under evolving COVID-19 public health guidelines, they typically work with partners to train members of impacted communities in water quality sampling and identify the types of toxins flowing through their streets, educate their neighbors and family concerning water quality indicators, and use data collected to advocate for and support a healthier environment. Please sign up to express your interest in volunteering when community engagement with the program resumes.  

CWW volunteers must be at least 18 years of age to volunteer.

